-- allium: 3
-- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium
--
-- Scope: the slot state machine and two scheduler gates that close
-- Bug C in the current shared-pool KV model. The contracts here
-- describe what the server's per-tick batch assembly may NOT
-- produce, and the two gating decisions in
-- examples/server/server-context.cpp that uphold the invariant.
--
-- Why this spec exists: Bug C — slot 0's decode token batched with
-- slot 1's full prefill in one llama_decode call — fires a
-- downstream mul_mat GEMV-vs-GEMM accumulation-order divergence
-- that produces wrong sampled tokens (~3e-3 per-element drift at
-- layer 0, see PHASE_NSTREAM_KV.md update (e) and (g)). The
-- kernel-level fix is infeasible (would require rewriting all
-- CUDA mul_mat to enforce GEMV-equivalent accumulation at every
-- batch size, with major perf cost). The closure that landed is
-- scheduler-level: prevent the mixed batch from ever forming.
-- This spec pins that closure as a contract so it cannot quietly
-- regress under future scheduler refactors.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entities for the server scheduler objects
--     (Slot, Tick, Batch, BatchToken).
--   - Enumerations for slot_state (matching slot_state in
--     server-context.h:14) and slot_command (server-context.h:21).
--   - Contracts for the two gating decisions:
--     PrefillSerialisationGate (v1, batch_pending_prompt) and
--     DecodeHoldGate (Bug C fix, add_sampled_tokens).
--   - System-wide invariants binding the slot lifecycle, the
--     batch composition rule, and the MixedBatchProhibition
--     property the downstream mul_mat path depends on.
--   - Open questions naming the choices the implementation
--     deferred (steady-state TG overlap recovery via per-stream
--     dispatch).
--
-- Excludes:
--   - The DFlash draft graph and the per-ubatch MTP-KV hook;
--     those are covered by mtp_fused_draft.allium and
--     mtp_ubatch_hook.allium. The contracts there describe what
--     ONE draft round / ubatch produces given the batch shape
--     this spec governs.
--   - The KV cache layout itself (per-stream cells, slot↔cells
--     mapping). Owned by specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium
--     once the 4D port lands; today's shared-pool model has no
--     dedicated spec because Bug C closure does not depend on its
--     details.
--   - The numerical bound between NP=1 and NP>1 slot output.
--     Owned by the perf-determinism harness
--     (scripts/test-production-np-determinism.sh) and the related
--     specs/deltanet/*. The current spec only asserts batch
--     COMPOSITION; numerical equivalence is downstream.
--   - The qnext_analyze_seq_pattern engine routing inside
--     llama_decode. Owned by qnext_multislot_dispatch.allium.
--     That spec governs what the engine does given a batch; THIS
--     spec governs which batches the server may assemble.

-- ============================================================
-- External entities — server scheduler objects
-- ============================================================

-- A server_slot, the per-session worker the HTTP layer assigns
-- arriving requests to. Lives at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:37-100.
external entity Slot {
    id: Integer
    state: SlotState
    command: SlotCommand
    released: Boolean
    n_prompt_tokens_processed: Integer
}

-- One update_slots() cycle. Each Tick produces at most one
-- llama_batch and at most one llama_decode call. The two gates
-- run inside update_slots — add_sampled_tokens at
-- server-context.cpp:3194 (decode-side), then
-- batch_pending_prompt at 3626 (prefill-side) — to assemble the
-- Batch that this Tick will dispatch.
external entity Tick {
    index: Integer
}

-- The llama_batch assembled in one Tick. May be empty (no slots
-- contributed), pure-prefill (one slot's prompt tokens), or
-- pure-decode (one decode token from each active PROCESSING
-- slot). The load-bearing property (MixedBatchProhibition) is
-- that it is NEVER both.
external entity Batch {
    tick: Tick
    n_tokens: Integer
}

-- One token in a Batch. is_prefill is true when the token was
-- contributed by batch_pending_prompt (a slot in
-- IDLE+LOAD_PROMPT). is_decode is true when contributed by
-- add_sampled_tokens (a slot in PROCESSING). Mutually exclusive
-- per-token; the spec asserts they are also mutually exclusive
-- across the whole Batch.
external entity BatchToken {
    batch: Batch
    slot: Slot
    is_prefill: Boolean
    is_decode: Boolean
}

-- ============================================================
-- Enumerations
-- ============================================================

-- Mirrors slot_state in ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:14-17.
enum SlotState { idle | processing }

-- Mirrors slot_command in ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:21-25.
enum SlotCommand { none | load_prompt | release }

-- ============================================================
-- Config
-- ============================================================

config {
    -- Maximum parallel slots the server may run. Mirrors
    -- --parallel N at start time, n_seq_max in cparams. The
    -- contracts hold for any value in [1, max_parallel_slots].
    -- The production geometry runs at 2 today; the spec is
    -- portable across 1..8.
    max_parallel_slots: Integer = 8
}

-- ============================================================
-- Contracts
-- ============================================================

-- The PrefillSerialisationGate — v1's at-most-one-prefill rule
-- in batch_pending_prompt. Lives at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3626 (function
-- entry) with the active_pp_slot_id selection at 3644-3681.
--
-- This is a PERFORMANCE policy, NOT a Bug C fix on its own. On
-- our hardware concurrent multi-slot prefill is ~4.8x slower
-- per-sequence than serial prefill due to attention-mask
-- blow-up at large n_tokens (commit 67878813). The gate enforces
-- the cheaper schedule. Bug C closure depends ALSO on the
-- DecodeHoldGate below; v1 alone is insufficient (measured: 20/20
-- failure post-v1 without the decode-side gate, see
-- PHASE_NSTREAM_KV.md (e)).
contract PrefillSerialisationGate {
    invoke: (slots: Set<Slot>, tick: Tick) -> Set<Slot>

    @invariant AtMostOneSlotContributesPrefillPerTick
        -- Within one Tick, at most one Slot may contribute prefill
        -- tokens to the Batch. Implementations select the slot
        -- that is mid-prefill (state=idle, command=load_prompt,
        -- n_prompt_tokens_processed > 0) first; if no slot is
        -- mid-prefill, the first slot in iteration order whose
        -- (state, command) = (idle, load_prompt) is chosen. The
        -- selection is stable within a Tick.

    @invariant NonSelectedPrefillSlotsAreSkipped
        -- Slots in (idle, load_prompt) that are not the active
        -- prefill slot for THIS Tick do not contribute any
        -- BatchToken to this Tick's Batch. They remain in
        -- (idle, load_prompt) and are eligible for selection in a
        -- subsequent Tick.

    @invariant ProcessingSlotsUnaffected
        -- The gate does not change the eligibility of slots in
        -- state=processing. Whether their decode tokens enter
        -- the Batch is governed by the DecodeHoldGate below.

    @guidance
        -- This gate is independent of Bug C correctness — it is
        -- a perf choice for our specific kernel suite. If a future
        -- platform's mul_mat can run parallel multi-slot prefill
        -- cheaply, the gate may be relaxed. Removing it does NOT
        -- by itself re-open Bug C, because the DecodeHoldGate
        -- (paired with this one) is what enforces the
        -- MixedBatchProhibition.
}

-- The DecodeHoldGate — the Bug C closure rule in
-- add_sampled_tokens. Lives at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3194 (function
-- entry); the gate body is the loop at 3205-3209 that
-- early-returns when any slot is (idle, load_prompt).
--
-- This IS the Bug C fix. Without it, when slot A finishes
-- prefilling and transitions to processing, slot B's still-
-- pending prefill lands in the same Batch as slot A's first
-- decode token — a mixed prefill+decode geometry that triggers
-- the downstream mul_mat GEMV-vs-GEMM accumulation order
-- divergence. The pre-fix stochastic 13% failure rate and the
-- v1-only 100% failure rate are both eliminated by adding this
-- gate. See PHASE_NSTREAM_KV.md update (e) for the bisect.
contract DecodeHoldGate {
    invoke: (slots: Set<Slot>, tick: Tick) -> Set<Slot>

    @invariant DecodeHeldWhilePrefillPending
        -- If any Slot in `slots` has (state, command) =
        -- (idle, load_prompt), the gate returns an empty set:
        -- NO Slot contributes decode tokens to this Tick's Batch.
        -- The implementation early-returns from
        -- add_sampled_tokens before any decode-token assembly.

    @invariant DecodeAdmittedWhenNoPrefillPending
        -- If no Slot has (state, command) = (idle, load_prompt),
        -- every Slot in state=processing whose decode token is
        -- ready contributes one BatchToken with is_decode=true,
        -- subject to the per-slot draft-batch contracts in
        -- mtp_fused_draft.allium for slots in speculative mode.

    @invariant BoundedStallByPrefillDuration
        -- A Slot in state=processing stalls for at most one
        -- prefill-duration when this gate fires. The gate has no
        -- multi-tick memory; the next Tick where no Slot is
        -- (idle, load_prompt) admits decode normally.

    @guidance
        -- This gate undoes v1's "TG-overlap preserved" intent
        -- (67878813 commit message): decodes now stall during any
        -- prefill, not just during the SAME slot's prefill. The
        -- cost is bounded by prefill duration per arrival;
        -- measured as ~6 s on test-pp-serialization.sh wall time
        -- vs the pre-fix theoretical lower bound. For sporadic-
        -- arrival workloads this is acceptable. For steady-
        -- arrival workloads, the recovery path is the n_stream KV
        -- port (PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_4D.md) — per-stream dispatch
        -- makes mixed batches impossible by construction, at
        -- which point this gate becomes redundant and is removed.
}

-- The lifecycle a Slot moves through across Ticks. Lives at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:534-538 (the
-- is_idle / is_available predicates), 578-582 (release path),
-- 1714 (LOAD_PROMPT assignment from incoming task), 3106-3107
-- (post-decode idle transition), 3953 (PROCESSING transition
-- after prefill completes).
contract SlotLifecycle {
    invoke: (slot: Slot) -> Slot

    @invariant InitialStateIdleNone
        -- A freshly-constructed Slot starts at
        -- (state, command, released) = (idle, none, false).

    @invariant LoadPromptOnTaskArrival
        -- When the server assigns an incoming task to a Slot
        -- (server-context.cpp:1714), the Slot transitions from
        -- (idle, none) to (idle, load_prompt). State stays idle
        -- until the prefill completes; command carries the
        -- "work pending" signal.

    @invariant ProcessingOnPrefillComplete
        -- When batch_pending_prompt has contributed the final
        -- chunk of the Slot's prompt to a Batch, the Slot
        -- transitions to (state=processing, command=none).
        -- n_prompt_tokens_processed reaches n_prompt_tokens at
        -- this point.

    @invariant IdleOnRelease
        -- When the Slot releases (server-context.cpp:578-582),
        -- it returns to (idle, none, released=true) and is
        -- eligible for reassignment.

    @invariant ReleasedFlagSetByReleasePathOnly
        -- The `released` field becomes true only via the explicit
        -- release path; it is never set by the prefill or decode
        -- gates. The flag carries one-Tick visibility to the HTTP
        -- layer that the Slot just finished a task.
}

-- ============================================================
-- Invariants — system-wide
-- ============================================================

-- The load-bearing property the whole spec exists to assert. For
-- any Batch the server dispatches in any Tick, no two
-- BatchTokens within that Batch carry one prefill flag and one
-- decode flag. The Batch is either pure-prefill (every token
-- has is_prefill=true) or pure-decode (every token has
-- is_decode=true) — never mixed.
invariant MixedBatchProhibition {
    for batch in Batches:
        for a in BatchTokensOf(batch):
            for b in BatchTokensOf(batch):
                a != b implies not (a.is_prefill and b.is_decode)
}

-- Companion to MixedBatchProhibition: a positive statement that
-- every Batch belongs to exactly one of the two pure categories
-- (or is empty). Implementations may dispatch a Batch of one
-- prefill chunk or a Batch of paired decode tokens but never a
-- mix.
invariant BatchCompositionInvariant {
    for batch in Batches:
        let tokens = BatchTokensOf(batch)
        tokens.count = 0
            or tokens.all(t => t.is_prefill)
            or tokens.all(t => t.is_decode)
}

-- A per-token consistency rule: a BatchToken is exactly one of
-- prefill or decode (or neither, in some degenerate cases the
-- spec does not constrain — e.g. ubatch padding tokens with no
-- slot binding). The flags are not both true on the same token.
invariant PerTokenFlagExclusivity {
    for t in BatchTokens:
        not (t.is_prefill and t.is_decode)
}

-- The slot-state side of MixedBatchProhibition: if any Slot is
-- in (idle, load_prompt) at the start of a Tick, the Tick's
-- Batch contains no decode tokens (the DecodeHoldGate fired).
invariant DecodeHoldImpliedByPendingPrefill {
    for batch in Batches:
        let tick = batch.tick
        let slots = SlotsAtTickStart(tick)
        slots.any(s => s.state = idle and s.command = load_prompt)
            implies BatchTokensOf(batch).all(t => not t.is_decode)
}

-- The prefill-side companion: at most one Slot's tokens appear
-- with is_prefill=true in any given Batch. Lifts
-- PrefillSerialisationGate.AtMostOneSlotContributesPrefillPerTick
-- to a system-wide property.
invariant AtMostOnePrefillSlotPerBatch {
    for batch in Batches:
        BatchTokensOf(batch)
            .where(t => t.is_prefill)
            .map(t => t.slot)
            .distinct
            .count <= 1
}

-- ============================================================
-- Open Questions
-- ============================================================

-- OQ-1: At what arrival rate does the DecodeHoldGate's TG-stall
--   become unacceptable? The current workload is sporadic single-
--   user requests; the stall is bounded by one prefill duration
--   per arrival. The PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_4D.md plan targets the
--   n_stream port (per-stream dispatch) as the recovery
--   path. Spec records the open question; resolution comes when
--   N3 of that plan lands and the gate can be removed.
--
-- OQ-2: Should the BatchCompositionInvariant be relaxed to allow
--   prefill chunks from MULTIPLE slots in one Batch under the
--   per-stream dispatch model? Once per-stream graph dispatch is
--   in place, mixed batches become impossible at the dispatch
--   level — but the invariant phrased per-Batch becomes vacuous
--   if every Batch is single-slot. Either restate as a per-
--   stream invariant or retire when n_stream lands. Plan file
--   (S1.b) covers the n_stream side.
--
-- OQ-3: Does the SLOT_COMMAND_RELEASE intermediate state need
--   its own lifecycle clause? Today it appears in slot_command
--   (server-context.h:24) but is transient (a few lines before
--   the release path clears it). Spec models it as a possible
--   value but does not constrain its lifetime. If a future
--   refactor uses it for cross-tick book-keeping, revisit.

-- ============================================================
-- Implementation notes
-- ============================================================

-- Code-side anchors (paths from yarn-agentic root):
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:14-17
--     — enum slot_state.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:21-25
--     — enum slot_command.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.h:37-100
--     — struct server_slot, including released / state / command
--       / n_prompt_tokens_processed.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:1714
--     — LOAD_PROMPT assignment from incoming task.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3194-3209
--     — add_sampled_tokens entry + DecodeHoldGate body.
--   ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:3626-3681
--     — batch_pending_prompt entry + PrefillSerialisationGate
--       (active_pp_slot_id selection).
--
-- Black-box helpers used inline in the invariants above (not in
-- `deferred` per project convention — they have no separate
-- .allium spec):
--   BatchTokensOf, SlotsAtTickStart, Batches, BatchTokens.
--
-- Test infrastructure to drive from this spec via allium:propagate
-- (planned as S4 in /home/llm/.claude/plans/cached-crunching-tiger.md):
--   - Property test that drives concurrent multi-slot prefill
--     against the server and asserts no Batch contains both
--     prefill and decode tokens. Should reproduce Bug C
--     deterministically when the DecodeHoldGate is disabled, and
--     verify the gate restores PASS.
--   - State-machine test that walks the SlotLifecycle transitions
--     and asserts the BatchCompositionInvariant after each
--     simulated arrival/Tick.

-- ============================================================
-- Related specs
-- ============================================================

-- mtp_fused_draft.allium
--   Covers ONE draft round's KV writes and DraftToken
--   production. Does NOT cover the scheduler gate that decides
--   which slots contribute to the round's batch. THIS spec
--   governs that gate. Composition: a Slot in state=processing
--   with speculative mode active contributes via the
--   FusedDraftStep contract of mtp_fused_draft.allium, but only
--   when DecodeHoldGate admits it.
--
-- mtp_ubatch_hook.allium
--   Covers per-ubatch MTP-KV updates during the verify forward.
--   Operates downstream of llama_decode; the batch shape THIS
--   spec governs determines the ubatch shape that one sees.
--
-- qnext_multislot_dispatch.allium
--   Covers the engine's per-block dispatch when one Batch
--   contains multiple seq_ids (CONTIGUOUS_BLOCKS pattern). With
--   the BatchCompositionInvariant in this spec, a Batch can
--   still be multi-seq (multiple slots' decodes paired in one
--   call). qnext_multislot_dispatch.allium then governs how the
--   engine splits the batch by seq_id for the per-block linear-
--   attn dispatch.
--
-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium (forthcoming, S1.b)
--   The 4D per-stream KV layout that will eventually make the
--   DecodeHoldGate redundant. When that spec lands and the port
--   is implemented, this spec's DecodeHoldGate contract is
--   marked retired and the gate code in add_sampled_tokens is
--   removed.
